# Agent Configuration
# This file is tracked by git and serves as the bootstrap pointer
# for AI agents. The actual framework files live in private/.agent/.
#
# IMPORTANT: After cloning this repo, run:
#   git clone https://github.com/michael2221807/ming_private.git private
#   private\setup_private_env.bat  (as Administrator)
#
# This will create directory junctions so .agent/ and .cursor/ are accessible.

# ============================================================
# PROJECT CONTEXT (for AI agents)
# ============================================================
# Tech Stack: Vue 3 + TypeScript + Webpack + Pinia + Tailwind CSS
# Dev Server: http://localhost:9091 (webpack devServer)
# API Proxy: /api -> http://localhost:8000
#
# Key Files:
#   src/utils/AIBidirectionalSystem.ts  - AI prompt assembly & response parsing
#   src/services/worldHeartbeatService.ts - Background world simulation
#   src/utils/locationUtils.ts - NPC location management
#   webpack.config.js - Build config, dev server, proxy
#
# Agent Framework Location:
#   Workflows: private/.agent/workflows/  (or .agent/workflows/ if junctions are set up)
#   Rules:     private/.agent/rules/      (or .agent/rules/ if junctions are set up)
#   Templates: private/.agent/templates/
#
# Available Workflows:
#   - setup-new-game.md    : Initialize new game test environment
#   - setup-load-game.md   : Load existing game save
#   - game-round.md        : Run one round of game generation
#   - debug.md             : Connect browser for debugging (port 9091)
#   - test.md              : Run linting and type checks
#   - commit.md            : Standardized git commit
#   - refactor.md          : Safe refactoring checklist
#   - review.md            : Code review checklist
#   - plan.md              : Feature planning template
#
# Private Repo: https://github.com/michael2221807/ming_private.git
#   Contains: .agent/, .cursor/, docs/, testing_gamedata/
#   Setup:    See SETUP.md for new machine instructions
#
# CRITICAL RULES:
#   - File imports (settings, saves, presets) require USER manual action.
#     Do NOT try to automate file picker interactions.
#   - If data is lost (e.g., after browser restart), STOP and ask the user
#     to re-import. Do not try to fix it programmatically.
#   - API keys must be entered by the user. Never store or commit API keys.
